---

<p>KATAPULT Design System supports the following native HTML form elements: <code>{{ '<form>' | escape }}</code>, <code>{{ '<button>' | escape }}</code>, <code>{{ '<input>' | escape }}</code>, <code>{{ '<textarea>' | escape }}</code>, and <code>{{ '<label>' | escape }}</code>.

<p>The following CSS classes are supported:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>.form-label</code></li>
  <li><code>.form-control</code> (for input as well as textarea elements)</li>
  <li><code>.form-select</code></li>
  <li><code>.form-check</code> (for checbkox and radio elements)</li>
  <li><code>.form-text</code></li>
  <li><code>.btn</code></li>
</ul>

<p>When combining several controls in a form, you can wrap the form controls with spacing class as a container such as <code>.mb-m</code> to keep the spacing consistent.</p>

<h2>Complete form example</h2>

{% snippet %}
<div class="mb-m">
  <label for="input-name" class="form-label">Name</label>
  <input id="input-name" class="form-control" type="text" placeholder="Text input">
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <label for="input-username" class="form-label">Username</label>
  <input id="input-username" class="form-control control-valid" type="text" placeholder="Text input" value="KATAPULT">
  <p class="form-text text-valid">This username is available</p>
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <label for="input-email" class="form-label">Email</label>
  <input id="input-email" class="form-control control-invalid" type="email" placeholder="Email input" value="hello@">
  <p class="form-text text-invalid">This email is invalid</p>
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <select class="form-select" aria-label="Default select example">
    <option selected>Open this select menu</option>
    <option value="1">One</option>
    <option value="2">Two</option>
    <option value="3">Three</option>
  </select>
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <label class="form-label">Message</label>
  <textarea class="form-control" placeholder="Textarea"></textarea>
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <div class="form-check">
    <input type="checkbox" value="" id="checkbox">
    <label for="checkbox">
      I agree to the <a href="#">terms and conditions</a>
    </label>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mb-m">
  <div class="form-check">
    <input id="radio-yes" type="radio" name="question">
    <label for="radio-yes">Yes</label>
  </div>
  <div class="form-check">
    <input id="radio-no" type="radio" name="question">
    <label for="radio-no">No</label>
  </div>
</div>

<div>
  <button class="btn btn-wonky btn-l">Submit</button>
  <button class="btn btn-text">Cancel</button>
</div>
{% endsnippet %}
